Introduction

This project is a graphical Rock, Paper, Scissors game developed using Python and Tkinter. It includes a rule-based AI that makes decisions based on the player’s previous moves. Initially, the AI plays randomly, but after a few rounds, it analyzes the player’s pattern and chooses a counter move. The game provides an interactive and user-friendly interface with scoring and round tracking.

Objectives
To develop an interactive game using Python GUI
To implement rule-based AI logic
To understand decision-making based on user behavior
To create a visually appealing interface
To enhance problem-solving and programming skills
Tools Used
Python (Programming Language)
Tkinter (GUI Library)
Random Module (for initial AI moves)
System Design

The system consists of two main parts:

Frontend (GUI): Built using Tkinter, includes buttons, labels, and frames for interaction
Backend Logic:
Stores player move history
AI analyzes last 3 moves
Decision logic selects counter move
Score and round management

Flow:
User Input → AI Decision → Result Calculation → Score Update → Display Output

Key Features
Rule-based intelligent AI
Colorful and user-friendly interface
Score tracking system
5-round gameplay
Move history display
AI decision explanation
Reset game option
Calculations / Logic
AI checks last 3 player moves
Counts frequency of each move
Finds most used move
Uses counter strategy:
Rock → Paper
Paper → Scissors
Scissors → Rock

Winning Rules:

Rock beats Scissors
Paper beats Rock
Scissors beats Paper

Score is updated based on each round result, and the final winner is decided after 5 rounds.
